{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f949830c-3496-437f-b6cc-ca7451a049e1","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```\n   dotnet add package xunit.runner.mtp\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable — Microsoft.Testing.Platform makes your test project a standalone app.\n\n> **Note:** `xunit.runner.mtp` requires **xUnit v2 2.9.3+** or **v3**, so your version is compatible. Make sure your .NET SDK is **8.0.400+** or **9.0.100+** for full `dotnet test` integration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe3a5667-d409-4dca-ba35-a59d13946d15","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge-based question, so I can answer directly.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"3416:7CA0B:74B4985:80FA3EB:69F3FA02"},"id":"24f04bc6-4f2e-4e26-92c4-04a42c9b3d80","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:38.125Z","parentId":"9606c30e-530a-466f-8631-0d3ca3c7ee7d"}
